Constructor Injection:

Spring Supports creating injection using parameterized

Scenario # 01 [three styles]
Style # 01
<constructor-args>  //thats mean only one filed of POJO in this case e.g private String name; only name
	<value> name </value>
</constructor-args>

Style # 02 [using as an property attribute]

<bean class="com.Springs.ConstructorInjection.Person" id="pers">
<constructor-args value ="samina"/> //be default its string
<constructor-args value =777 type = "int"/>
</bean>


Style # 03 [Using c-schema "c for constructor access", "p for property p-schema"] 



For Reference Data Type

<constructor-args>
	<ref bean = " "/>
</constructor-args>